Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at a meeting about the fight against hate and antisemitism. She thanked Halie for her leadership and commitment, and emphasized the importance of living openly and supporting each other in the face of hate. Harris expressed concern about the rise of hate and antisemitism in the country, and highlighted her past work in prosecuting hate crimes. She quoted Coretta Scott King, saying that the fight for justice and equality must be fought and won with each generation. Harris urged vigilance and not taking progress for granted. She also praised the organization for their activism in the midterms and stressed the importance of responsible leadership and empathy. Harris called for lifting others up and finding common ground, and thanked everyone for their work and optimism.